The Nsukka, Enugu State country home of the President General of the Ohanaeze Nd’Igbo, Chief Nnia Nwodo, was on Sunday bombed by unidentified persons. It was gathered that the explosion, which razed parts of the building at Ukehe town, in Nsukka‎, was triggered by an Improvised Explosive Device. The Enugu State Police Public Relations Officer, Mr. Ebere Amaraizu, who confirmed the development, said that the police had already commenced ‎investigations to unravel the circumstances surrounding the incident. Details later… 